data.text:
PHOTO: Rhylee, Bradley, Mahki, George and Mikah at the National Museum of Australia.

by CPS PUBLICITY OFFICER

CPS Year 6 students have recently returned from Canberra where they visited Parliament House, Questacon, National Art Gallery and The National Electoral Education Centre, just to name a few!

The students left Coonamble on Monday 22nd July and returned after a full week on Friday 26th July.

PHOTO: Jannali, Kalani and Daniel visited the High Court of Australia.
